@node Tool
  
         Well actually there is only one tooltype (not exactly :)
       This tooltype automatically select the type of calculator
       according to it's value (on prog. startup).
       
       Values :   - 0 for Ti82
                  - 1 for Ti83
                  - 2 for Ti85
                  - 3 for Ti86
       @{b}           
       THIS ENTRY MUST BE THE FIRST OF ALL !!! AND THE VALUE MUST
       BE THE FIRST CHARACTER. @{ub}All other character and/or 
       tooltype will simply be ignored !!
       
       If you think I could add some tooltypes then please send
       me your ideas and I'll write a real tooltype parser !
       
       
@endnode

@node Meaning

	One of the LED lit when the Amiga is on the line and the
	other lit when the Ti is on line. It happens when the Ti
	or the Amiga is sending (one for the amiga and the other
	for the Ti).

@endnode

